        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Well, I know we've been around this mullberry bush before, but let's hit play on that CD again.  I have heard people say lots of the following:

1)  They'd destroy their Zheart before selling their pre-nerf CoS
2)  They'd destroy <<insert item of choice>> before getting rid of their pre-nerf CoS.

I have looked at the stats on the Zheart, and it is a freaking amazing item.  Then I looked at the price...ouch....and put my food stamps back in my pocket.

Price checks on Xev server for Pre-nerf CoS (when you can find them) are 30 - 40kpp.  Price check on Zheart is 75kpp.

Now, why are people willing to destroy a Zheart worth 75kpp before destroying an average priced 35kpp item?  Is it because (this is my theory) the Zheart still drops and you will have another opportunity to get a Zheart?  That's sort of what I'm thinking....even though the Zheart is worth soo much more, it's attachment becomes less because it still drops and is replaceable by guild hunting.

I have a pre-nerf CoS, but I don't have a Zheart.  I would like a Zheart, but don't have raid force to help me get one.  Nor do I have the kpp required.  Therefore, I have this propostition for Necros (that don't yet have pre-nerf CoS) that go on Raids capable of replacing their Zhearts:

WTT (xev server) Pre-nerf CoS for Zlander's Heart

<<cringes from fear of flames>>
HtH

[url="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=322851"][img]http://www3.telus.net/hayzeus/SnowBunny4.jpg [/img][/url]
[/quote]</textarea><br>
        </td>
